FERC Electric MBR Tariff
1. Availability. Coyanosa Gas Services Corporation (Seller) makes electric energy, capacity and ancillary services available under this tariff to any purchaser, except as prohibited below.
2. Applicability. This tariff is applicable to all sales of electrical energy, capacity, or ancillary services by Seller, not otherwise subject to a particular Rate Schedule or tariff of Seller.
3. Ancillary Services. PJM: Seller offers regulation and frequency response service, energy imbalance service, and operating reserve service (which includes spinning, 10-minute, and 30-minute reserves) for sales into the market administered by PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. ("PJM") and, where the PJM Open Access Transmission Tariff permits, the self-supply of these services to purchasers for a bilateral sale that is used to satisfy the ancillary services requirements of the PJM Office of Interconnection.
4. Rates. All sales shall be made at rates established by agreement between the purchaser and Seller.
5. Seller Category. Seller is a Category 1 seller, as defined in 18 C.F.R. Section; 35.36(a).
6. Limitations and Exemptions Regarding Market-Based Rate Authority. The Commission has granted Victoria International LTD, now Coyanosa Gas Services Corporation, waiver of Subparts B and C of Part 35 of the Commission's Regulations requiring the filing of cost-of-service information, except for Sections 35.12(a), 35.13 (b), 35.15 and 35.16; Part 41, Part 101, and Part 141 of the Commission's Regulations concerning accounting and reporting requirements, except for Sections 141.14 and 141.15; and blanket authorization under Part 34 of the Commission's regulations for all future issuances of securities and assumptions of liability. (Coyanosa Gas Services Corporation, formerly Victoria International LTD, Docket Nos. ER05-757-000, 001 and 002 at p. 3-5, 2005) (unpublished letter order).
7. Compliance and Commission Regulations. Seller shall comply with the provisions of 18 C.F.R. Part 35, Subpart H, as applicable, and with any conditions the Commission imposes in its orders concerning Seller's market-based rate authority, including orders in which the Commission authorizes Seller to engage in affiliate sales under this tariff or otherwise restricts or limits the Seller's market-based rate authority. Failure to comply with the applicable provisions of 18 C.F.R. Part 35, Subpart H, and with any orders of the Commission concerning Seller's market-based rate authority, will constitute a violation of this tariff.
8. Other Terms and Conditions. All other terms and conditions of sales shall be established by agreement between purchaser and Seller.
9. Effective Date. This tariff is effective upon such date as is set by the Commission.
